# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# Type can be:
#   feat     - A new feature
#   fix      - A bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation only changes
#   style    - Code style changes (formatting, semicolons, etc)
#   refactor - Code refactoring without changing functionality
#   perf     - Performance improvements
#   test     - Adding missing tests
#   chore    - Changes to build process or auxiliary tools
#   ci       - Changes to CI configuration files
#
# Scope: The part of the codebase affected (e.g., api, cli, auth, db)
#
# Subject: Short description (50 chars max)
#   - Use imperative mood: "Add" not "Added"
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#
# Body: Detailed description (wrap at 72 chars)
#   - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
#   - Include motivation and contrast with previous behavior
#
# Footer: Reference issues and breaking changes
#   - Closes #123
#   - BREAKING CHANGE: description
#
# Example:
# feat(api): add researcher collaboration endpoint
#
# Add new endpoint to fetch collaboration network for researchers.
# This enables visualization of research partnerships.
#
# Closes #42
